column5: ME  Finally got to trade in the suckers and shakers for something that took me for a real good run. He tried to run me into an over hanging tree down stream but i had my waders on, and made a quick jump off the bank and into the creek. Why is it that the one's that get off always run up stream but the one's that are hooked good run down stream, so you have to fight them and the current?    PS: Thanks Geoff for the secret spot!!!!!
Congrats much better than a sucker SBK
Nice one Dann That huge tail must put alot of power into her run.  P,S, Do the dishes for gawds sake man !!!
Glad you got a good one me-brother-from-a-different-muta
Nice fish Dann! Congrats.  Paul - I think the dishes are done, just drip drying. Looks like my sink.

LOL They are done, its a double sink and Kelly had to do the dishes so i could have the one sink for fish cleaning.  The fish was pretty much spent by the time the fight was over, and i hate wasting a fish so he will be dinner real soon.
Nice fish and the first photo I have seen from up North in short sleeves.   Art
What Geoff is giving away secret spots now hey where is my pm with a spot?   Nice going skeeter
Ok, fine.  Here you go jose...  43.568452,-79.633369
